        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>Sensitivity: 

Our primary goal is the gas dynamics and morphology (eg tidal filaments etc) of the molecular gas in the disrupted disks of the merging galaxies.  The 3-2 CO line is ideal because emission is strong in PDRs, XDRs, and shocks.  From JCMT observations, we have the flux integrated in the 13" beam, ~155 Jy km/s.   Taking the line width of ~90 km/s, this implies a mean flux of 1.7 Jy in the 13" beam.   The worst case scenario is that the flux is uniformly distributed, in which case the flux in a 0.4" beam will be 1.6 mJy.   With a sensitivity of 0.0015 mJy, this gives S/N of 1.   However, in any given velocity channel it is certain that the emission will not be uniformly distributed over the 13" JCMT beam, and so we can anticipate good S/N.  

Imaging:   The CARMA CO 1-0 emission (Fig 2) shows emission that could be extended as much as 7", and that most of the emission is in a 20" region.   Thus we choose a 7-point Nyquist sampled mosaic to cover a 20" rectangle.   We request spatial coverage to 7", necessitating two configurations including the compact configuration.

Correlator Setup: The primary line is the CO 3-2 line, with a velocity range with wings that extend over nearly 1400 km/s; thus the 1875 MHz bandwidth (1660 km/s) is adequate.     The hanning smoothed resolution is ~1 kms km/s but we would likely we smooth to 10km/s as this would be appropriate for discriminating between simulations and scenarios.  Our main  science goal is to get 10km/s channels for which this choice of the spw is adequate.    HCO+ would be observed with a similar setup.     Due to the location of the CS 7-6 line, it is not possible to get 1875 MHz bandwidth centered on the line, so the CS is at one extreme and the other part of the 1875 MHz window will be used for continuum.   The fourth correlator window covers continuum.

Calibration:  System defined is chosen - nothing special needed.

Bandpass Accuracy - There is no special need for additional bandpass accuracy.

Schedule / Time constraints: None

Data Rate:  Safely within limits.

Special constraints:  None
</prj:justificationText>
