    <prp:code/>
    <prp:abstract>We propose to use ALMA observations of CO (3-2) to map the dynamics of the 2 closest dual AGN Mrk739 and NGC6240 at both galactic (1-3kpc) and nuclear 50-300pc scales . Both of these objects have plate scales of 1"=500pc, perfectly positioned for ALMA observations  over this range of scales and have lower signal to noise and spatial resolution CO 1-0 data from CARMA. Our exposures are based on JCMT CO(3-2) data with an angular resolution of 15"

We have 2 science goals
1) to understand why these 2 mergers are dual AGN, while the vast majority major mergers have, at best, one black hole active and
2)   compare the dynamics of the detailed simulations of merging black holes to the data.

We have chosen to observe in  CO (3-2) because it traces the molecular gas which is thought to be responsible for 'feeding' the black holes and because it is produced via a wide range of mechanisms (PDRs, shocks and XDRs) and thus can trace a wide variety of physical conditions.
</prp:abstract>
